---
import SiteLayout from "../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
	title="About App Trust Proxy"
	description="Project editions, naming, and safety principles for App Trust Proxy."
	bodyClass="sub-page"
>
	<section class="page-hero">
		<div class="page-hero__inner">
			<img src="/app-trust-proxy-icon.png" alt="" width="88" height="88" decoding="async" />
			<h1>About App Trust Proxy</h1>
			<p>
				App Trust Proxy is a product family for authorized local application traffic inspection. The first public edition is App Trust Proxy Core, a free open source runtime for repeatable proxy labs.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section__inner edition-grid">
			<article class="edition-card">
				<p class="section-kicker">Open source</p>
				<h2>App Trust Proxy Core</h2>
				<p>
					Core is the MIT licensed server project. It runs the local proxy services, web console, certificate tooling, capture store, rules, scripts, interaction prompts, and profile import or export features.
				</p>
				<a class="text-link" href="/docs/#start-core">Run Core</a>
			</article>
			<article class="edition-card">
				<p class="section-kicker">Desktop</p>
				<h2>App Trust Proxy</h2>
				<p>
					App Trust Proxy is the desktop app name. The Mac app is still under development and will build on the same trusted local traffic workflow with native desktop polish.
				</p>
				<a class="text-link" href="/#desktop">View desktop status</a>
			</article>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section section--tint">
		<div class="section__inner narrow">
			<p class="section-kicker">Principles</p>
			<h2>Trust, repeatability, and control</h2>
			<p>
				The project is designed around explicit domain allowlists, visible modifications, portable profiles, and local ownership of generated certificates and captured data.
			</p>
			<p>
				Use it only when you have permission to inspect the traffic. Keep generated certificates, private keys, captures, scripts, and profiles private.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section__inner timeline">
			<div class="section-heading">
				<p class="section-kicker">Roadmap</p>
				<h2>Current project focus</h2>
			</div>
			<ol class="timeline-list">
				<li>
					<strong>Core runtime</strong>
					<span>Stabilize the server, web console, Docker setup, no Docker runner, and profile system.</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Documentation</strong>
					<span>Make setup, domain rules, raw answers, interactive prompts, and safe local operation easy to share.</span>
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Mac app</strong>
					<span>Develop the branded desktop app for users who want a native App Trust Proxy experience.</span>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>
